lign: baseline; background-color: transparent;">They last thoughout the ages </span></pre>\n<pre dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 32px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;">My grandfather''s favourite fairytale </span></pre>\n<pre dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 32px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;">Or the science gathered among the pages </span></pre>\n<pre></pre>\n<pre dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 32px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;">And these words bring people together </span></pre>\n<pre dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 32px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;">Language unites and sets us free </span></pre>\n<pre dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 32px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;">But it is same words that bind us </span></pre>\n<pre dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 32px; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; vertical-align: baseline; background-color: transparent;">As when two different cultures meet. </span></pre>\n<pre>\n\n</pre>', '', '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', '', '', '', '2015-06-06 23:12:29', '2015-06-06 17:42:29', '', 0, 'http://blog.thebookhub.in/?p=225', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(146, 1, '2015-04-25 19:37:28', '2015-04-25 14:07:28', 'Another Saturday night. The whole world seems to be lost in the dance floor; making temporary friends and washed out memories. Tantalizing. With a sombre mind and a half-hearted attempt to "dress for the occasion", you grab the handle of the door and stop midway. The One beckons you and you know there is no further questioning.\r\n\r\nYou delve into the familiar pages of your all-time favourite book.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://blog.thebookhub.in/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/stock-footage-fireplace-and-a-book.jpg"><img class="  wp-image-143 aligncenter" src="http://blog.thebookhub.in/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/stock-footage-fireplace-and-a-book-300x168.jpg" alt="stock-footage-fireplace-and-a-book" width="431" height="246" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nDrowning in nostalgia and mingled with the hope of finding something new, this book has and always will be a part of your soul. The pages bear unforgettable scents, each more homely than the last. The words pour out of you as if you lived to write the chapters in this story. You create irreplaceable bonds with every character. As you grow older, you discover new insights and perceptions about the story, the character. You might have hated the antagonist but now you admire his stand. Teary eyed, you cursed the author for the death of your favourite character but now you understand why which makes the book even more beautiful.  When you finished reading it the first time, you knew this love affair would not be fading away.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href="http://blog.thebookhub.in/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/cropped-shutterstock_86389951.jpg"><img class="  wp-image-144 aligncenter" src="http://blog.thebookhub.in/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/cropped-shutterstock_86389951-300x123.jpg" alt="cropped-shutterstock_86389951" width="512" height="220" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWine and coffee tastes better when accompanied with the One. Reality does not compare when you immerse yourself in the world you wish you could see. People who like the One automatically become your best friends. Different books by the same author may or may not (mostly not) be as good as this work of gold. No matter what people say, the movie will NEVER be better.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href="http://blog.thebookhub.in/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Writers-Cabaret-Option-1.jpg"><img class="  wp-image-145 aligncenter" src="http://blog.thebookhub.in/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/Writers-Cabaret-Option-1-200x300.jpg" alt="Writers Cabaret Option 1" width="306" height="451" /></a>\r\n\r\nFor those of you who haven''t experienced the euphoria of finding your favourite book, keep looking. For it is a key to a secret world that only you know of. In this dark world of despair and betrayal, no one can destroy the liaison between man and book.\r\n\r\nWho''s the One for you?\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'The One', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '140-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-04-25 19:37:28', '2015-04-25 14:07:28', '', 140, 'http://blog.thebookhub.in/140-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
