r can understand when one gets to touch the book in all its dimensions. Technology and e-books can never replace real books that way. Tactility is something that helps the reader build a connection with what he’s about to read, according to psychological studies, it stimulates his curiosity as humans respond and react mostly to touch. \r\n\r\nBooks also have a crucial role in forming a person’s mindset. For instance: a person indulging way too often in fiction may end up being way too imaginative and mentally immature. Romance novels often make the reader develop the notion that love is a beautiful feeling (which it is, no doubt) but they may also cause the reader that love stories have a perfectly happy ending as usually portrayed in books. It could cause the person to mistake ‘like’ for ‘love’ and fall in love with the ‘concept of love’. It is amazing no doubt but one should always balance out the proportion in which he/she reads every genre, that’s the moral. (All said from personal experience)\r\n\r\nAlso, most importantly, books are an invaluable medium of communication. Talking and reaching out to people, sending across your views, opinions, stories and ideas with feedback in the form of critic’s review and the readership.  Apart from this, when people read, it surely raises some questions, which makes them interact with others who have read the same book. Interaction leads to bonding and it goes on.\r\n\r\nLooking at all this, we could reiterate the fact that books have more than just one aspect; social, personal, psychological and technical. An in-depth understanding of everything above would help us realize exactly how important are books in our lives. \r\nFor these very reasons, books are invaluable treasures for mankind that not only need to be preserved but also promoted, loved and respected. They are beautiful gifts that deserve to be cherished, beating hearts of book-lovers.\r\n\r\nIn conclusion, I would end with a well known saying,\r\n“They say humans only live one life, but a reader has already lived a billion.”<strong></strong> <a href="http://blog.thebookhub.in/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/books-1.jpg"><img src="http://blog.thebookhub.in/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/books-1-300x200.jpg" alt="books 1" width="300" height="200" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-64" /></a>\r\n', 'More than just ''Books''', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '60-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-04-03 23:04:20', '2015-04-03 17:34:20', '', 60, 'http://blog.thebookhub.in/60-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(72, 1, '2015-04-08 15:20:50', '2015-04-08 09:50:50', '<p>For some, it is their favorite pastime whereas, for some, reading is the best way to take their minds off of the troubles of daily life. Each one of us needs an activity that can calm our minds and rejuvenate our body after we have spent the whole day running from one place to another, either completing errands, or living up to our boss’ expectations. Reading is an activity that can only benefit the reader and can never harm him if done for the purpose of recreation.</p>\r\n<p>A recent biological study claims that for each new thought that a human brain thinks of, a new branch is created inside it, which results in an increase in the speed of impulse transfer, hence improving the brain’s processing speed. Now keep this fact in mind and think of an avid reader- a reader who indulges himself in reading materials that make him imagine things he has never imagined before. Each imagination, a new thought. Each new thought, a new brain branch. No wonder most of the geniuses that the world has ever seen had/have reading as an integral part of their daily lives.</p>\r\n<p>Studies have also shown that staying mentally stimulated can slow the progress of (or possibly even prevent) Alzheimer’s and Dementia, since keeping your brain active and engaged prevents it from losing power.</p>\r\n<p>Reading can be of various forms. People read newspapers, journals, novels, blogs, and various other rich text. However, reading a novel is the most consuming of all. This is simply because if a person starts reading a novel of his interest, it is nearly impossible for him to leave it without completing it, as each line of a novel says a new story. Each new line drowns the reader into deeper and deeper thoughts. This is the kind of craving that reading creates.</p>\r\n<p>The answer to the question that what a novel transforms a person into, is not a simple one. It obviously is not something involving calculus, but it is complex because there are so many things that a person changes into while reading, that it is quite difficult to document it in one place. However, by the means of this article, I will try my best to throw as much light as possible on the various transformations.</p>\r\n<p>As I already mentioned earlier, many people use novel reading as a recreational way for <b>stress reduction</b>. A person, if inculcates a regular reading habit, he is less susceptible to breaking down under pressure than his counterparts who are not in a habit of reading. No matter how much stress he has at work, in his relationships or in other issues faced in everyday life, all that just slips away when he involves himself into a great story. A well-written novel has the capability to transport a person under stress to other realms, allowing him to drain his problems out of his mind and to relax. In addition to the relaxation that accompanies reading a good book, it is possible that the subject being read by a person can bring about <b>immense inner peace and tranquility</b>.Reading spiritual texts can lower blood pressure and bring about an immense peace, while reading self-help books has helped people suffering from certain mood disorders and mild mental illnesses.</p>\r\n<p>One of the most sought after gems in a person’s language is his <b>vocabulary</b>. A novel can transform an average language user into someone who has a vast vocabulary and has the capability to impress people listening to him or reading his work by the use of such subtle but highly impactite words. A large vocabulary also boosts a person’s self-esteem, his confidence, and may also prove as a very helpful aid in his career, especially if his job requires communicating with people.  In addition to increased vocabulary, a novel improves a person’s <b>writing skills</b>. This can directly be inferred from the fact that an increase in vocabulary means better usage of words and thus, improved writing. Observing the cadence, fluidity and writing styles of other authors influences one’s own work. Just as musicians influence one another, and painters use techniques established by previous masters, so do writers learn how to craft prose by reading the works of others.</p>\r\n<p>Besides vocabulary, who can forget to mention what novels give a person the most - <b>knowledge</b>. Everything a person reads, fills his head with new bits of information, which might come in handy anytime. Also, a thing to remember is that a person might lose everything in life, his job, his house, his money - but no one has the power to take away his knowledge from him.</p>\r\n<p>A book is said to be one of the easiest and the best ways for <b>memory improvement</b>. But how can storytelling improve memory? This is because each novel has an assortment of characters; each character has its own history, ambitions, and nuances, as well as the various arcs and sub-plots weaving their way throughout the novel which ought to be remembered if the whole of the story has to be understood.</p>\r\n<p>In our Internet-crazed world, attention is drawn in a million different directions at once as we multi-task throughout the day. But when a person reads a book of his interest, his entire attention is focused just on the story - the rest of the world just falls away, and the reader immerses in every fine detail he is absorbing. One should try reading for 15-20 minutes every day before starting his daily activities and he’ll be surprised at the increased amount of focus he’s able to give to all activities he involves himself in.</p>\r\n<p>At last, it is clear that reading transforms a person into someone entirely different. The icing on the cake, all these benefits come for free! Sure some of us buy books, but most books are available either for free or at meager costs at local libraries, or on the Internet. There’s a genre for every literate person on our planet, and whether your taste lies in classical literature, poetry, fashion magazines, religious texts, biographies, young adult books or romantic novels, there’s something out there to capture your curiosity and imagination. So step away from meaningless activities for a little while, crack open a book or an e-book, and replenish your soul for a little while.</p>\r\n', 'Books full of words, a life full of experiences', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '45-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-04-08 15:20:50', '2015-04-08 09:50:50', '', 45, 'http://blog.thebookhub.in/45-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(123, 1, '2015-04-18 20:30:40', '2015-04-18 15:00:40', 'In those pages was written a story untold,\r\nA treasure more invaluable then silver, platinum or gold.\r\nWith every turned page, a magical spell was cast,\r\nA beautiful essence that would forever last.\r\nA reader and a book-lover’s guilty pleasure,\r\nOur love for books go beyond all measures.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://blog.thebookhub.in/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/download1.jpg"><img src="http://blog.thebookhub.in/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/download1.jpg" alt="download" width="298" height="169" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-124" /></a>\r\n\r\nSo, let’s talk about that one reason why we’re all following and reading this blog right now – Books!\r\nReaders are to books what dogs are to bones. You could just push them into a room full of books or a library and never expect them to come out. A nice cup of coffee and a quiet place is all they need to fulfill their wishes. Gift them books to win their hearts or make their birthdays perfect. The way we feel about books is the way Belle is ‘Beauty and the Beast’ reacts when the Beast shows her the library. Funny but true. The smell of the new pages and the ones that are ancient with age; it’s like a harmless drug for readers. A million stories that spark off our imagination and apart from imparting education, they help us to discover the fact that words may be just mundane like other things to many people but for us, they’re like beautiful galaxies woven and spun together to form a flawlessly stunning universe. \r\n\r\n<a href="http://blog.thebookhub.in/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/images-1.jpg"><img src="http://blog.thebookhub.in/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/images-1.jpg" alt="images (1)" width="194" height="259" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-125" /></a>\r\n\r\nThere are words for every genre – that’s their beauty. There’s something for everything. Technology may be a boon to mankind and you could say it’s a blessing for those who don’t like carrying books around in their bags and take the care of maintaining them, but then every coin has a flip side: the screen of ‘Kindle’ could crack for all you know, one click of a button and you could just lose your opportunity of reading. You could drop them and damage them. E-books stored on laptops and computers; they have a chance of getting lost with the hard-drive crash or any technological glitch for that matter. Handling them with care is another clause that comes with technological products. Not to forget the strain on your eyes when you keep staring at a screen for hours while reading and then comes along another problem – ‘Kindle’ runs on battery that can expire or run out of charge or even get damaged. Without the battery, ‘Kindle’ is basically a box with books that can’t be accessed. Books, you can carry them anywhere, anytime in any condition; no worries of the ‘Kindle’ not being able to withstand extreme temperatures. Books, you fix them up with tape, put some classic binding and glue them up; all at a reasonable cost. No need to go to a technician and spend a thousand bucks and wait for days to just read a few books!!  I mean c’mon! Paper is so much better than pixels!\r\n1.	True ownership of a book:\r\n\r\n<a href="http://blog.thebookhub.in/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/images.jpg"><img src="http://blog.thebookhub.in/wp-content/uploads/2015/04/images-300x168.jpg" alt="images" width="300" height="168" class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-126" /></a>\r\n\r\nIt’s true that you can own a book and an ‘e-book’. But even the ownership is different in nature. Book makes you have a feel of the ‘physical ownership’, in hard-copy. It becomes a part of yourself. You can hug it and go to sleep. Sit peacefully on a beach, reading a book, with the waves kissing your body and receding, no worries of dropping your book in the water and losing it because the water seeped into the hardware and destroyed it. It’s your constant companion. Scribble notes and ideas, literally and symbolically mark your territory over it. The highlights and markings are one aspect. Then comes the interaction and engaging process with the book.\r\n The plus point – there are visible marks that you’ve bonded with your book. Only if you have a proper book, will people ever know you’ve read it; or anyone else for that matter. You see bent and ‘dog-eared’ pages, a shaking and loose book spine, signs of age and use. People will come to know that the reader has been impacted by the book, the story has had an effect on their lives. On the other hand, send an e-book to someone else; if you get it back, you’ll see the highlights and notes gone, because that’s just how technology is. The ownership belongs to you or your device, not to the book. Last but not the least, when you often to go to a library and see an old book, flip through its pages. See the notes and ideas written over the pages. You’ll get an idea of what kind of experiences different people had with the book and how it has made a mark on those lives. This can never be reproduced in an e-book format.\r\n\r\n2.	Loan  a Book:\r\nYou ask me why I hate e-books; they CAN’T be loaned! They have some kind of digital rights management involved which bonds a book to a particular owner. On buying a Kindle book, you could have a copy of it on your device but then again! There comes the system of linking the devices with various accounts. It’s all painful technological processes everywhere just to give yourself the pleasure of reading a great story. In case of books, you can loan one or two or any number. That’s the best – anywhere, any way, any time and how much ever. In case of Kindle, you have to loan your entire reading device; basically, either you loan everything or nothing at all. Then again, even if an e-book doesn’t have any digital management rights, loaning it is very different from actual loaning. It’s actually ‘duplicating’ a book. When you loan someone a book, they actually witness your experience with it. There’s a level of trust, intimacy and shared experience in loaning books which can’t be found in electronic books.\r\n\r\n3.	A single tasking device. \r\nA book is inherently opposed to multi-tasking. Not more than one or two tasks can be performed while reading it. This indirectly implies that a reader can devote nearly 90% of his attention to the story that he/she is reading. No distraction, no problem.  This allows the reader to have the best possible reading experience and actually enjoy it. E-books on the other hand, are technological devices crafted in such a way that multi-tasking is made possible. Stored in I-Pads or anything else for that matter, e-books contain hyper-links and built-in dictionary and many other applications somehow related to reading which drive the reader away from the wholesome reading experience. They buzz, beep and disengage the reader in many ways.\r\n\r\n4.	One can buy a used book.\r\nWalk down a street and see if you can see even a single e-book store as compared to outlets selling used books. E-books can never be USED, let’s face it. They stay cold, unblemished and untouched but only duplicated for years to come. Their prices never change, they can never be dug out of boxes like long lost treasure and never suddenly turn up like unexpected old gifts from us to us. They can never be loaned or resold. They stay fresh, unused and forever sustained. There are NO  rare first editions or special editions. A used book will be a vestige of the past but irreplaceable and vintage.\r\n\r\nBecause books are the BEST inventions till date!\r\n', 'Why books will always be magical', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'why-books-will-always-be-magical', '', '', '2015-04-18 23:44:40', '2015-04-18 18:14:40', '', 0, 'http://blog.thebookhub.in/?p=123', 0, 'post', '', 1),
